            <h3 class="demo-subtitle">Auto Selecting a Radio Option</h3>
            <p>To automatically select an option, toggle the <span class="code-inline">aria-checked="false"</span> attribute to be <span class="code-inline">aria-checked="true"</span>. This can be changed by the user if they select another option.</p>


            <div class="fieldset-demo">
                <div class="field">
                    <h4 class="field-group-label">Radio Group Label</h4>
                    <ul class="radio-group list-stripped" role="radiogroup" aria-labelledby="field-group-label">
                        <li>
                            <input id="radio-5" class="radio" type="radio" value="5" role="radio" aria-checked="false" name="radio" />
                            <label for="radio-5" class="radio-label">Option 1</label>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <input id="radio-6" class="radio" type="radio" value="6" role="radio" aria-checked="true" name="radio" />
                            <label for="radio-6" class="radio-label">Option 2</label>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <input id="radio-7" class="radio" type="radio" value="7" role="radio" aria-checked="false" name="radio" />
                            <label for="radio-7" class="radio-label">Option 3</label>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
